M|Reac|tx|A structured repository for creating and maintaining rc Best Practices optimized for ag and LLMs.
M|Stru|it|`rules/` - Individual rule files (one per rule)
M|Stru|it|`_sections.md` - Section metadata (titles, impacts, descriptions)
M|Stru|it|`_template.md` - Template for creating new rules
M|Stru|it|`area-description.md` - Individual rule files
M|Stru|it|`src/` - bd scripts and utilities
M|Stru|it|`metadata.json` - Document metadata (version, organization, abstract)
M|Stru|it|__`ag.md`__ - Compiled output (generated)
M|Stru|it|__`tst-cases.json`__ - tst cases for LLM evaluation (generated)
M|Gett|1. I|
M|Gett|tx|```bash
M|Gett|tx|pnpm install
M|Gett|tx|```
M|Gett|2. B|
M|Gett|tx|```bash
M|Gett|tx|pnpm bd
M|Gett|tx|```
M|Gett|3. V|
M|Gett|tx|```bash
M|Gett|tx|pnpm validate
M|Gett|tx|```
M|Gett|4. E|
M|Gett|tx|```bash
M|Gett|tx|pnpm extract-tests
M|Gett|tx|```
M|Crea|tx|1. cp `rules/_template.md` to `rules/area-description.md`
M|Crea|2. C|
M|Crea|it|`async-` for Eliminating Waterfalls (Section 1)
M|Crea|it|`bundle-` for Bundle Size op (Section 2)
M|Crea|it|`server-` for Server-Side perf (Section 3)
M|Crea|it|`client-` for Client-Side Data Fetching (Section 4)
M|Crea|it|`rerender-` for Re-render op (Section 5)
M|Crea|it|`rendering-` for Rendering perf (Section 6)
M|Crea|it|`js-` for JavaScript perf (Section 7)
M|Crea|it|`advanced-` for Advanced Patterns (Section 8)
M|Crea|tx|3. Fill in the frontmatter and cn
M|Crea|tx|4. Ensure you have clear examples w/ explanations
M|Crea|tx|5. Run `pnpm bd` to regenerate ag.md and tst-cases.json
M|Rule|Each|
M|Rule|tx|```markdown
M|Rule|tx|---
M|Rule|titl|Rule Title Here
M|Rule|impa|md
M|Rule|impa|Optional description
M|Rule|tags|tag1, tag2, tag3
M|Rule|tx|---
M|Rule|tx|Brief explanation of the rule and why it matters.
M|Rule|**In|**
M|Rule|tx|```ts
M|Rule|tx|// Bad code example
M|Rule|tx|```
M|Rule|**Co|**
M|Rule|tx|```ts
M|Rule|tx|// Good code example
M|Rule|tx|```
M|Rule|tx|Optional explanatory text after examples.
M|Rule|Refe|[Link](https://example.com)
M|File|it|Files starting w/ `_` are special (excluded from bd)
M|File|- Ru|`area-description.md` (e.g., `async-parallel.md`)
M|File|it|Section is automatically inferred from filename prefix
M|File|it|Rules are sorted alphabetically by title within each section
M|File|it|IDs (e.g., 1.1, 1.2) are auto-generated during bd
M|Impa|it|`ct` - Highest priority, major perf gains
M|Impa|it|`hi` - sig perf improvements
M|Impa|it|`md-hi` - Moderate-hi gains
M|Impa|it|`md` - Moderate perf improvements
M|Impa|it|`lo-md` - lo-md gains
M|Impa|it|`lo` - Incremental improvements
M|Scri|it|`pnpm bd` - Compile rules into ag.md
M|Scri|it|`pnpm validate` - Validate all rule files
M|Scri|it|`pnpm extract-tests` - Extract tst cases for LLM evaluation
M|Scri|it|`pnpm dv` - bd and validate
M|Cont|When|
M|Cont|tx|1. Use the correct filename prefix for your section
M|Cont|tx|2. Follow the `_template.md` structure
M|Cont|tx|3. Include clear bad/good examples w/ explanations
M|Cont|tx|4. Add appropriate tags
M|Cont|tx|5. Run `pnpm bd` to regenerate ag.md and tst-cases.json
M|Cont|tx|6. Rules are automatically sorted by title - no need to manage numbers!
